noun','home','A sliding box-shaped compartment in a piece of furniture.','The scissors are in the top drawer of the desk.'),(3122,'cloth','тряпка / ткань','UNCOMMON',204,'en-ru','noun','home','A piece of fabric used for cleaning or wiping surfaces.','Wipe the counter with a damp cloth.'),(3123,'mould','плесень','UNCOMMON',204,'en-ru','noun','home','A fungus that grows in damp conditions.','Check the bathroom walls for mould every few weeks.'),(3124,'drain','слив / канализация','UNCOMMON',204,'en-ru','noun','home','A pipe that carries away waste water.','The drain is blocked — we need to call a plumber.'),(3125,'thermostat','термостат','UNCOMMON',204,'en-ru','noun','home','A device that automatically controls temperature.','Set the thermostat to 20 degrees to save energy.'),(3126,'plug','вилка / пробка','UNCOMMON',204,'en-ru','noun','home','A device that connects an appliance to an electrical socket.','Pull out the plug before you leave the house.')""")
                db.execSQL("""INSERT OR IGNORE INTO words(id,original,translation,rarity,setId,languagePair,pos,semanticGroup,definition,example) VALUES (3128,'film','фильм','COMMON',206,'en-ru','noun','cinema','A story recorded as moving images shown on a screen.','Let us watch a film tonight — any preferences?'),(3129,'actor','актёр','COMMON',206,'en-ru','noun','cinema','A person who performs a role in a film or play.','The lead actor won an award for his performance.'),(3130,'cinema','кинотеатр','COMMON',206,'en-ru','noun','cinema','A building where films are shown to the public.','The cinema in town has twelve screens.'),(3131,'seat','место (в зале)','COMMON',206,'en-ru','noun','cinema','A chair in a theatre or cinema.','We reserved seats in the front row.'),(3132,'screen','экран','COMMON',206,'en-ru','noun','cinema','The flat surface on which films are projected.','The image on the screen was incredibly sharp.'),(3133,'audience','зрители / аудитория','UNCOMMON',206,'en-ru','noun','cinema','The people gathered to watch a performance.','The audience applauded enthusiastically at the end of the play.'),(3134,'role','роль','UNCOMMON',206,'en-ru','noun','cinema','A character played by an actor.','She landed the lead role in the new thriller.'),(3135,'performance','выступление / спектакль','UNCOMMON',206,'en-ru','noun','cinema','An act of presenting a play to an audience.','The evening performance starts at eight o''clock.'),(3136,'rehearsal','репетиция','UNCOMMON',206,'en-ru','noun','cinema','A practice session for a performance.','The director called an extra rehearsal before opening night.'),(3137,'script','сценарий','UNCOMMON',206,'en-ru','noun','cinema','The written text of a film or play.','She spent months writing the script for the short film.'),(3138,'interval','антракт','UNCOMMON',206,'en-ru','noun','cinema','A pause between acts of a play.','We bought ice cream during the interval.'),(3139,'comedy','комедия','UNCOMMON',206,'en-ru','noun','cinema','A film or play intended to make the audience laugh.','He prefers comedy to drama when choosing a film.'),(3140,'act','акт / действие','UNCOMMON',206,'en-ru','noun','cinema','A division of a play or opera.','The twist in the final act shocked everyone.'),(3141,'flower','цветок','COMMON',208,'en-ru','noun','gardening','The colourful part of a plant that produces seeds.','She planted flowers along the path to the front door.'),(3142,'seed','семя','COMMON',208,'en-ru','noun','gardening','A small object produced by a plant from which a new plant can grow.','Sow the seeds in early spring for summer flowers.'),(3143,'grass','трава','COMMON',208,'en-ru','noun','gardening','Low green plants that cover lawns and fields.','Cut the grass before it gets too long.'),(3144,'soil','почва / земля','COMMON',208,'en-ru','noun','gardening','The top layer of the earth in which plants grow.','Mix compost into the soil before planting.'),(3145,'plant','растение','COMMON',208,'en-ru','noun','gardening','A living organism that grows in soil and has leaves.','Water the plant every two days in summer.'),(3146,'garden','сад / огород','COMMON',208,'en-ru','noun','gardening','An outdoor area where plants are grown.','She spent the weekend tidying the garden.'),(3147,'water','поливать','COMMON',208,'en-ru','verb','gardening','To pour water onto plants or soil.','Remember to water the tomatoes every evening.'),(3148,'grow','выращивать','COMMON',208,'en-ru','verb','gardening','To cultivate a plant or allow it to develop.','We grow our own herbs on the kitchen windowsill.'),(3149,'leaf','лист растения','COMMON',208,'en-ru','noun','gardening','A flat green part of a plant that grows from a stem.','The leaves turned yellow in autumn.'),(3150,'tree','дерево','COMMON',208,'en-ru','noun','gardening','A tall plant with a wooden trunk and branches.','The apple tree in the garden produces fruit every year.'),(3151,'dig','копать','UNCOMMON',208,'en-ru','verb','gardening','To break up and move soil with a tool.','Dig the soil to a depth of 30 cm before planting potatoes.'),(3152,'rake','грабли','UNCOMMON',208,'en-ru','noun','gardening','A garden tool with a long handle and teeth for gathering leaves.','Rake up the fallen leaves and add them to the compost.'),(3153,'pot','горшок (цветочный)','UNCOMMON',208,'en-ru','noun','gardening','A container in which plants are grown.','Move the pot indoors before the first frost.'),(3154,'trim','подрезать / стричь','UNCOMMON',208,'en-ru','verb','gardening','To cut away unwanted parts of a plant to keep it tidy.','Trim the hedge once a month in summer.'),(3155,'bloom','цвести / цветение','UNCOMMON',208,'en-ru','verb','gardening','To produce flowers; the state of flowering.','Roses bloom from late spring through to autumn.'),(3156,'root','корень','UNCOMMON',208,'en-ru','noun','gardening','The part of a plant that grows underground and absorbs water.','The roots of the old oak tree spread far underground.'),(3157,'branch','ветка','UNCOMMON',208,'en-ru','noun','gardening','A part of a tree that grows from the main trunk.','Prune the lower branches to let more light into the garden.'),(3158,'petal','лепесток','UNCOMMON',208,'en-ru','noun','gardening','One of the coloured parts of a flower.','Rose petals fell gently onto the path.'),(3159,'stem','стебель','UNCOMMON',208,'en-ru','noun','gardening','The main stalk of a plant that supports its leaves and flowers.','Cut the stem at an angle so the flower can absorb water.'),(3161,'email','электронная почта','COMMON',209,'en-ru','noun','internet','Electronic messages sent over the internet.','Send me an email with the details of the meeting.'),(3162,'profile','профиль','COMMON',209,'en-ru','noun','internet','A personal page on a social network showing your information.','Update your profile with a recent photo.'),(3163,'post','пост / публикация','UNCOMMON',209,'en-ru','noun','internet','A piece of content published on a social media platform.','Her post about the trip got hundreds of likes.'),(3164,'share','делиться / репостить','UNCOMMON',209,'en-ru','verb','internet','To repost or distribute content to your own followers.','If you liked the article, share it with your friends.'),(3165,'like','лайк','UNCOMMON',209,'en-ru','noun','internet','A positive reaction button on social media.','The video got over a million likes in one day.'),(3166,'comment','комментарий','UNCOMMON',209,'en-ru','noun','internet','A written response left below a post or video.','Leave a comment below if you have any questions.'),(3167,'chat','чат','UNCOMMON',209,'en-ru','noun','internet','Real-time text communication over the internet.','We stayed in touch through a group chat.'),(3168,'video call','видеозвонок','UNCOMMON',209,'en-ru','noun','internet','A phone call in which you can see the other person on screen.','They had a video call every Sunday to catch up.'),(3169,'feed','лента (новостей)','UNCOMMON',209,'en-ru','noun','internet','A continuously updated list of posts on a social media platform.','Scroll through your feed to see the latest updates.'),(3170,'account','аккаунт','UNCOMMON',209,'en-ru','noun','internet','A registered user profile on a website or app.','Create an account to access all the features.'),(3171,'gas','газ','COMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','A substance that expands to fill any container.','Carbon dioxide is a gas released when fuels burn.'),(3172,'liquid','жидкость','COMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','A substance that flows freely and takes the shape of its container.','Water is the most common liquid on Earth.'),(3173,'solid','твёрдое тело','COMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','A substance with a fixed shape that does not flow.','Ice is the solid form of water.'),(3174,'metal','металл','COMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','A material such as iron that conducts electricity and heat.','Iron is a metal that rusts when exposed to moisture.'),(3175,'heat','тепло / нагрев','COMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','Energy that causes a rise in temperature.','Applying heat to the substance causes it to melt.'),(3176,'test','опыт / испытание','COMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','A procedure carried out to check a scientific hypothesis.','The litmus test shows whether a solution is acid or alkaline.'),(3177,'base','основание','UNCOMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','A chemical that neutralises an acid to form a salt.','Sodium hydroxide is a strong base used in many reactions.'),(3178,'salt','соль (химическая)','UNCOMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','A compound formed when an acid reacts with a base.','Common table salt is sodium chloride.')""")
                db.execSQL("""INSERT OR IGNORE INTO words(id,original,translation,rarity,setId,languagePair,pos,semanticGroup,definition,example) VALUES (3179,'oxygen','кислород','UNCOMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','A colourless gas that makes up about 21% of the atmosphere.','Oxygen is essential for combustion and respiration.'),(3180,'hydrogen','водород','UNCOMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','The lightest element, which combines with oxygen to form water.','Hydrogen burns easily and is used as a fuel.'),(3181,'carbon','углерод','UNCOMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','An element found in all living things and fossil fuels.','Carbon forms the backbone of organic molecules.'),(3182,'solution','раствор','UNCOMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','A liquid mixture in which a substance is evenly dissolved.','Add the salt to the water to make a saline solution.'),(3183,'mixture','смесь','UNCOMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','A combination of two or more substances not chemically joined.','Sand and water form a mixture, not a compound.'),(3184,'experiment','эксперимент','UNCOMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','A scientific test to discover or prove something.','The experiment confirmed the hypothesis about reaction rates.'),(3185,'dissolve','растворять(ся)','UNCOMMON',219,'en-ru','verb','chemistry','To mix completely with a liquid and become part of it.','Sugar dissolves quickly in warm water.'),(3186,'burn','гореть / сжигать','UNCOMMON',219,'en-ru','verb','chemistry','To undergo combustion, producing heat and light.','The magnesium ribbon burns with a bright white flame.'),(3187,'particle','частица','UNCOMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','A very small piece of matter.','Heat causes particles to move faster.'),(3188,'density','плотность','UNCOMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','The mass of a substance per unit of volume.','Gold has a much higher density than water.'),(3189,'formula','формула (химическая)','UNCOMMON',219,'en-ru','noun','chemistry','A combination of symbols representing a chemical compound.','The formula for water is H2O.'),(3190,'markdown','уценка / снижение цены','RARE',240,'en-ru','noun','retail','A reduction in the selling price of an item.','The markdown on winter coats was fifty percent.'),(3191,'turnover','товарооборот / выручка','RARE',240,'en-ru','noun','retail','The total sales revenue of a business over a period.','Annual turnover rose by twelve percent last year.'),(3192,'shrinkage','потери товара (кражи, порча)','RARE',240,'en-ru','noun','retail','The loss of inventory due to theft or damage.','Shrinkage accounts for two percent of annual revenue.'),(3193,'margin','маржа / прибыль','RARE',240,'en-ru','noun','retail','The difference between the cost of a product and its selling price.','The profit margin on fresh produce is typically low.'),(3194,'markup','наценка','RARE',240,'en-ru','noun','retail','The amount added to the cost price to set the selling price.','A 40% markup covers overhead costs and profit.'),(3195,'stock-take','инвентаризация','RARE',240,'en-ru','noun','retail','The process of counting all items held in a store.','The store closes on Sunday night for the monthly stock-take.'),(3196,'net weight','вес нетто','RARE',240,'en-ru','noun','retail','The weight of a product excluding its packaging.','The net weight of cereal in the box is 500 g.'),(3197,'supplier','поставщик','RARE',240,'en-ru','noun','retail','A company that provides goods or materials to a retailer.','The supplier delivered the new stock on Tuesday morning.'),(3198,'supply chain','цепочка поставок','EPIC',240,'en-ru','noun','retail','The entire sequence of processes involved in producing and distributing a product.','Disruptions to the supply chain raised prices globally.'),(3199,'footfall','посещаемость (магазина)','EPIC',240,'en-ru','noun','retail','The number of people entering a shop or shopping centre.','Footfall increased sharply during the Christmas period.'),(3200,'loss leader','товар-приманка','EPIC',240,'en-ru','noun','retail','A product sold at a low profit to attract customers.','Supermarkets use milk as a loss leader to bring in shoppers.'),(3201,'soldering iron','паяльник','RARE',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A hand tool used to melt solder and join electronic components.','Use the soldering iron carefully to avoid burning the circuit board.'),(3202,'lathe','токарный станок','RARE',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A machine that rotates a workpiece so a cutting tool can shape it.','The lathe turned the wooden block into a smooth cylinder.'),(3203,'jigsaw','лобзик','RARE',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A power tool with a narrow blade used to cut curves in wood.','Use a jigsaw to cut the curved shapes for the shelf supports.'),(3204,'angle grinder','болгарка','RARE',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A handheld power tool used for cutting and grinding.','Wear safety goggles when using an angle grinder.'),(3205,'plane','рубанок','RARE',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A woodworking tool used to shave thin layers from a surface.','Run the plane along the door edge to make it fit the frame.'),(3206,'rasp','рашпиль','RARE',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A coarse file with raised teeth for shaping wood.','Shape the curve with a rasp before sanding smooth.'),(3207,'rivet','заклёпка','RARE',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A metal pin used to join two pieces of material permanently.','Aircraft panels are held together with thousands of rivets.'),(3208,'brace','распорка / скоба','RARE',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A device that holds two things firmly together in position.','Fit a diagonal brace to stop the frame from racking.'),(3209,'blowtorch','паяльная лампа','EPIC',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A device that produces a hot flame for soldering or stripping paint.','The plumber used a blowtorch to sweat the copper joints.'),(3210,'tile cutter','плиткорез','EPIC',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A tool used to score and snap ceramic tiles to size.','Score the tile with the tile cutter before snapping it along the line.'),(3211,'router','фрезер','EPIC',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A power tool used to hollow out or shape an area of wood.','Use the router to cut the groove for the shelf panel.'),(3212,'pneumatic drill','отбойный молоток','EPIC',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A power tool driven by compressed air for breaking up hard surfaces.','The workers used a pneumatic drill to break up the old concrete.'),(3213,'torque wrench','динамометрический ключ','LEGENDARY',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A wrench that applies a specific torque to a fastener.','Always tighten wheel bolts to the specified torque with a torque wrench.'),(3214,'mitre saw','торцовочная пила','LEGENDARY',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A power saw used to make accurate crosscuts and mitre cuts in wood.','Cut the skirting boards to 45 degrees with a mitre saw.'),(3215,'calibrate','калибровать','LEGENDARY',241,'en-ru','verb','tools','To adjust an instrument to make it accurate.','Calibrate the torque wrench before each use.'),(3216,'dovetail','ласточкин хвост (соединение)','LEGENDARY',241,'en-ru','noun','tools','A strong interlocking joint used in furniture-making.','The drawer sides were joined with hand-cut dovetails.'),(3217,'gala','торжественный вечер','RARE',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','A festive occasion with special entertainment or performances.','The charity gala raised over fifty thousand pounds.'),(3218,'banquet','банкет','RARE',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','A grand formal meal for many people.','The state banquet was attended by heads of government.'),(3219,'memorial','траурный / памятный','RARE',242,'en-ru','adj','celebrations','Relating to remembering a person or event from the past.','A memorial service was held at the cathedral.'),(3220,'inaugural','инаугурационный','RARE',242,'en-ru','adj','celebrations','Relating to the beginning of an important role or period.','The inaugural ceremony marked the opening of the new museum.'),(3221,'pageant','красочное шествие','RARE',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','An elaborate public entertainment or display.','The medieval pageant attracted thousands of spectators.'),(3222,'rite','обряд','RARE',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','A religious or solemn ceremony or act.','Baptism is an important rite in many Christian traditions.'),(3223,'ovation','овация','RARE',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','A long enthusiastic round of applause.','The audience gave the conductor a standing ovation.'),(3224,'festivity','торжество / праздничность','RARE',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','The celebration of something in a joyful manner.','The street was full of festivity on New Year''s Eve.'),(3225,'eulogy','надгробная / хвалебная речь','EPIC',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','A speech praising someone, typically at their funeral.','He delivered a moving eulogy that brought many to tears.'),(3226,'jubilee','юбилей (особый)','EPIC',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','A special anniversary, especially a 25th or 50th.','The company celebrated its golden jubilee with a grand party.'),(3227,'consecration','освящение / посвящение','EPIC',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','The act of making something sacred in a religious ceremony.','The consecration of the new church drew hundreds of worshippers.'),(3228,'commemoration','увековечение памяти','EPIC',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','An official ceremony that preserves the memory of a person or event.','The commemoration of the battle took place at dawn.')""")
                db.execSQL("""INSERT OR IGNORE INTO words(id,original,translation,rarity,setId,languagePair,pos,semanticGroup,definition,example) VALUES (3229,'pomp','пышность / помпа','EPIC',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','Ceremony and splendid display associated with great occasions.','The royal wedding was celebrated with great pomp and pageantry.'),(3230,'benediction','благословение','EPIC',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','The utterance of a blessing, especially at the end of a service.','The priest gave a benediction at the close of the ceremony.'),(3231,'exuberance','ликование / бурная радость','EPIC',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','The quality of being full of energy, excitement, and cheerfulness.','The crowd greeted the victory with unrestrained exuberance.'),(3232,'panegyric','панегирик','LEGENDARY',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','A public speech praising someone enthusiastically.','The ambassador delivered a panegyric in honour of the retiring diplomat.'),(3233,'solemnity','торжественность','LEGENDARY',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','The quality of being serious and dignified in tone or manner.','The solemnity of the occasion demanded respectful silence.'),(3234,'extravaganza','экстраваганца','LEGENDARY',242,'en-ru','noun','celebrations','An elaborate and spectacular entertainment or production.','The closing ceremony was a musical extravaganza.'),(3235,'magistrate','магистрат / мировой судья','RARE',243,'en-ru','noun','professions','A civil officer who administers the law.','The case was heard by a magistrate in the local court.'),(3236,'underwriter','андеррайтер','RARE',243,'en-ru','noun','professions','A person who assesses and assumes financial risk.','The underwriter evaluated the insurance application carefully.'),(3237,'osteopath','остеопат','RARE',243,'en-ru','noun','professions','A practitioner who treats conditions by manipulating the musculoskeletal framework.','The osteopath treated her chronic back pain with gentle manipulation.'),(3238,'surveyor','геодезист / инспектор','RARE',243,'en-ru','noun','professions','A person who measures and maps land or inspects buildings.','The surveyor identified several structural problems with the property.'),(3239,'metallurgist','металлург','RARE',243,'en-ru','noun','professions','A scientist who studies the properties and processing of metals.','The metallurgist analysed the composition of the alloy.'),(3240,'toxicologist','токсиколог','EPIC',243,'en-ru','noun','professions','A scientist who studies the adverse effects of chemicals on living organisms.','The toxicologist determined the cause of the poisoning.'),(3241,'neurologist','невролог','EPIC',243,'en-ru','noun','professions','A doctor specialising in disorders of the nervous system.','The neurologist ordered an MRI to investigate the symptoms.'),(3242,'forensic scientist','судебный эксперт','EPIC',243,'en-ru','noun','professions','A scientist who applies scientific methods to criminal investigations.','The forensic scientist analysed the evidence collected at the scene.'),(3243,'geophysicist','геофизик','EPIC',243,'en-ru','noun','professions','A scientist who studies the physical properties of the Earth.','The geophysicist used seismic waves to map underground structures.'),(3244,'cryptographer','криптограф','EPIC',243,'en-ru','noun','professions','A specialist in the theory and practice of writing or solving codes.','The cryptographer designed an encryption algorithm for the secure service.'),(3245,'biostatistician','биостатистик','LEGENDARY',243,'en-ru','noun','professions','A specialist who applies statistics to biological and medical research.','The biostatistician designed the clinical trial analysis plan.'),(3246,'palaeontologist','палеонтолог','LEGENDARY',243,'en-ru','noun','professions','A scientist who studies fossil plants and animals.','The palaeontologist discovered a previously unknown species of dinosaur.'),(3247,'numismatist','нумизмат','LEGENDARY',243,'en-ru','noun','professions','A collector or expert in coins and medals.','The numismatist authenticated the rare Roman denarius.'),(3248,'lexicographer','лексикограф','LEGENDARY',243,'en-ru','noun','professions','A person who compiles dictionaries.','Samuel Johnson was one of the most famous lexicographers in English history.'),(3249,'damp-proof course','гидроизоляционный слой','RARE',244,'en-ru','noun','home','A layer of waterproof material in a wall that prevents moisture rising.','The damp-proof course must be intact to keep the walls dry.'),(3250,'joinery','столярные изделия','RARE',244,'en-ru','noun','home','Items made by a joiner, such as doors, windows, and staircases.','The quality of the joinery throughout the house was excellent.'),(3251,'cavity wall','двойная стена (с полостью)','RARE',244,'en-ru','noun','home','A wall built of two leaves with a gap between them for insulation.','The cavity wall insulation keeps the house warmer in winter.'),(3252,'downpipe','водосточная труба','RARE',244,'en-ru','noun','home','A pipe that carries rainwater from a gutter to a drain.','The downpipe was blocked with leaves, causing the gutter to overflow.'),(3253,'rendering','штукатурная отделка фасада','RARE',244,'en-ru','noun','home','A coat of plaster applied to the outside of a wall.','The exterior rendering was cracked and needed replacing.'),(3254,'dado rail','горизонтальный молдинг','RARE',244,'en-ru','noun','home','A horizontal moulding fixed to a wall at about waist height.','The dado rail divides the wallpaper from the painted lower half.'),(3255,'ridge tile','конёк (крыши)','RARE',244,'en-ru','noun','home','A tile used to cover the ridge of a roof.','Several ridge tiles were dislodged by the storm.'),(3256,'fascia board','подшивочная доска (карниза)','RARE',244,'en-ru','noun','home','A board fixed horizontally at the edge of a roof to support the guttering.','Replace the rotten fascia board before fitting new gutters.'),(3257,'alcove','ниша (в стене)','EPIC',244,'en-ru','noun','home','A recess in the wall of a room, often used to fit shelving.','They built bookshelves in the alcoves on either side of the fireplace.'),(3258,'architrave','наличник / обналичка','EPIC',244,'en-ru','noun','home','The moulding around a door or window frame.','Sand down the architrave before applying a fresh coat of paint.'),(3259,'soffit','подшив / потолок свеса','EPIC',244,'en-ru','noun','home','The underside of an architectural element such as an arch or overhang.','The soffit beneath the stairs was painted white to brighten the space.'),(3260,'coving','потолочный карниз / лепнина','EPIC',244,'en-ru','noun','home','A curved junction between the wall and ceiling, usually moulded.','Decorative coving was added to the living room to give it a period feel.'),(3261,'fenestration','остекление / расположение окон','EPIC',244,'en-ru','noun','home','The arrangement of windows and doors in a building.','The fenestration on the south facade maximises natural light.'),(3262,'inglenook','ниша у камина','LEGENDARY',244,'en-ru','noun','home','A recess on either side of a large fireplace.','The inglenook fireplace with its wooden beams gave the cottage great character.'),(3263,'wainscoting','дощатая обшивка стен','LEGENDARY',244,'en-ru','noun','home','Wooden panelling lining the lower part of an interior wall.','The dining room featured original Victorian wainscoting painted in dark green.'),(3264,'voice-over','закадровый голос','RARE',245,'en-ru','noun','cinema','A narration recorded for a film but not seen on screen.','The documentary used a voice-over to explain the historical context.'),(3265,'storyboard','раскадровка','RARE',245,'en-ru','noun','cinema','A series of drawings showing the planned sequence of shots in a film.','The director sketched the storyboard before shooting began.'),(3266,'score','саундтрек / музыкальная тема','RARE',245,'en-ru','noun','cinema','The music composed for a film or theatrical production.','The score by Ennio Morricone perfectly captured the mood of the f